    "John \"Coz\" Colgrove is cofounder and chief visionary officer of data management and storage company Pure Storage.",
    "He helped launch the company in 2009 and took it public on the New York Stock Exchange in 2015.",
    "Colgrove, who owns 4% of Pure Storage, pushed for an outside CEO from the very beginning, because he was adamant about staying in a technical role.",
    "Before cofounding Pure Storage, he joined data storage company Veritas Technologies in 1989 as a founding engineer and worked there through its IPO in 1993 and Symantec's $13.5 billion acquisition of Veritas in 2005.",
    "Colgrove joined Palo Alto-based venture capital firm Sutter Hill Ventures in 2009 as an entrepreneur-in-residence where he met his eventual Pure Storage cofounder John Hayes."
